race.comment: WATERSPORTS (15) stayed on well when resuming and then again last time when just outdashed off a much steadier tempo before getting going when it was all too late. Willow should be able to keep her in touch from the low draw this time and with a truer tempo to run at. Just needs a split at the right time. DARK SIMBA (6) was a touch plain in Sydney but they went no pace at all there. The return run said that he would be winning races this time in. LEG DRIVE (5) has already won his races this time around. Two of his past three and the latest came over the course and distance. Stuck at it there and not hopeless again. AHHA AHHA (11) also comes off winning around here last time. No wins this prep for PORTER (2) and he threw up a poor one last time but he was going well prior and the talent is there.
